metadata.description:
This piece of generative art is not your retirement plan. It's just a fun, color, inexpensive piece of generative art that you can revisit in the years to come, as the world of NFTs and crypto evolves and matures. Maybe buy a few and send them to your friends when they get their first Tezos wallet. Send one to your mom.

Press the space bar when in Live view to export an image of the current frame.

metadata.name: BLEND #140
metadata.description:
Blend are generative loops and animated pieces creating a shape with a digital painting effect.
The size, position and motion frequency of trails are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 
You can press spacebar to stop the animation.

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Brussels (Belgium).  

Features :
	- Between 10 and 80 trails, impacted or not by an update of their radius and randomly filled
	- 4 directions - from North West (NW), from North East (NE), from North or from West.
	- Duration between 16 and 24 seconds
	- Amplitude of the shape on X and Y
	- Offset delay: between 0.1 and trails count, manage the delay between each trails movement
	- Noise count : number of points to create the noise effect on background
	- Background color :  color randomly get from 1 of 151 color themes

metadata.name: filaments #57
metadata.description:
A simulation using differential growth, imitating simple life-forms resembling bacteria.
The points in each filament attract and repel each other, to form doodle-like shapes in the end.

metadata.name: Above (The Infinite) #249
metadata.description:
This project is an animated extension of my previous work in static generative tilings.
It explores how visual complexity can arise from the combination of simple building blocks.

This work is written in OpenGL Shading Language (GLSL) and requires a compatible GPU to function.

There are five features exposed:
- Palette: The color palette used (out of four possible).
- Palette Cycle: The color cycling method used.
- Phase Transforms: How many additional phase transformation functions are applied in addition to the core set of six.
- Blend Mode: How phase transformation are blended. Either strictly based on time or via a combination of screen coordinates and time.

The animation can be stopped and started by pressing the space key.

This is my genesis fx(hash) project.

Twitter: @jeffpalmer
Site: https://jpalmer.dev

metadata.name: Composition #3 Patchwork Quilt #153
metadata.description:
Abstract, non-square(!) composition based on textural strokes and noise. There are a lot of possible combinations with all of the features! 50% chance of two different palette sets. 50% chance to have a brush textured background, and a 50% chance of it being horizontal or vertical. The quadtree rectangles are based on poisson disc sampling based on a simplex noise field. 90% of the compositions will be smaller boxes, and 10% will be large. For each box, there is a 10% chance that it will be oriented opposite of the rest.

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot.
